The paper discusses the use of evolutionary learning to create topologically flexible networks that can perform steady-state input-output operations. This falls under the category of neural networks and evolutionary computation (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the controllability and multiplexing of these networks, which relates to systems and control (cs.SY). The use of learning methods and transfer learning suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the study's focus on biologically inspired computing suggests a connection to systems and information theory (cs.SI).
